Definition.WordDefinition: Duchy \Duch"y\ (d[u^]ch"[y^]), n.; pl. {Duchies}. [F. duch['e], OF. duch['e]e, (assumed) LL. ducitas, fr. L. dux. See {Duke}.] The territory or dominions of a duke; a dukedom. [1913 Webster]
duchy n : the domain controlled by a duke or duchess [syn: {dukedom}]
